2 (5) A person who violates this section is subject to a civil penalty as follows:
3 (a) a fine of not less than $75 or more than $149 for a first violation; and
4 (b) a fine of not less than $150 or more than $250 for a second or subsequent violation.
5 (6) A peace officer who stops a motor vehicle for an alleged violation of this section may not take
6 possession of or otherwise inspect a portable wireless communication device in the possession of the operator
7 unless otherwise authorized by law.
8 (7) The regulation and use of portable wireless communication devices while operating a motor
9 vehicle are of statewide concern.
10 (8) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
11 (a) "Internet data" includes but is not limited to any conceivable application in which information is
12 conveyed by the internet that requires the visual or tactile attention of the user. The term includes social media
13 in any form.
14 (b) (i) "Portable wireless communication device" means a cellular telephone, a portable telephone,
15 a text-messaging device, a personal digital assistant, a stand-alone computer, a global positioning system
16 receiver, or a substantially similar portable wireless device that is used to initiate or receive communication,
17 information, or data.
18 (ii) The term does not include a radio, a citizens band radio, a citizens band radio hybrid, a
19 commercial two-way radio communication device or its functional equivalent, a subscription-based emergency
20 communication device, a prescribed medical device, an amateur or ham radio device or in-vehicle security, or a
21 navigation or remote diagnostics system.
22 (c) "Stand-alone electronic device" means a portable device other than a portable wireless
23 communication device that stores audio or video data files to be retrieved on demand by a user.
